title: Sturgis West navigates title
text: Posted Oct. 12, 2015 at 10:08 PM By Cape Cod Times Posted Oct. 12, 2015 at 10:08 PM » Social News MARLBORO - JD Snowman’s course record led the Sturgis West boys cross country squad to victory at the Charter School Championship Invitational at the Advanced Math & Science Academy on Monday. Snowman’s course record on the 3.2 mile run, a time of 18:16, led the Navigators over Innovation Academy, Advanced Math & Science Academy at Sturgis East. Snowman was followed by Liam Furey (third, 18:47), Sean Glynn (fifth, 19:14), Dan Burke (eighth, 19:39), Alex Sheremet (15th, 20:54), Brendan Glynn (19th, 21:14) and Sam Furtado (25th, 22:35). The Sturgis West girls finished just behind the host Advanced Math & Science and ahead of Sturgis East. Katie Kane led the way for the Navigators with a sixth place finish in 23:12. Also for Sturgis West girls was Bri Newell (seventh, 23:16), Emma Schneider (10th, 23:50), Mary Kane (12th, 23:59) and Angela Cote (27th, 30:26). FIELD HOCKEY Dennis-Yarmouth 8, Nantucket 0: Summer Walsh, Hannah Morse and Aoife Daly had two goals each for the Dolphins in a shutout win over the Whalers on the island. Walsh added two assists on the game for Dennis-Yarmouth (6-3-1) with Anna McGaffigan adding a goal and two assists, Taylor Conley adding one goal and one assist and Julia Paini and Abby Anderson adding one assist each. Lindsey Gallagher and Grace Bent (two saves) split time in net for the Dolphins en route to the shutout. Nantucket drops to 5-6. Martha’s Vineyard 6, Sharon 0: Belle Dinning had three goals and Lee Hayman added a goal and four assists in the Vineyarders win in Oak Bluffs. Dinning helped pull Martha’s Vineyard, now 7-2-1, within a point of a South Sectional tournament berth, giving the island club a 1-0 lead at half on Hayman’s first assist. The Vineyarder found their scoring touch after the break, with Dinning scoring two quick goals, both on assists from Hayman, for a 3-0 lead. Sophie McCarron made it 4-0 on Hayman’s fourth assist, before Kylie Hatt scored on a Genny Kent assist, then assisted Hayman for the 6-0 final. Julie Levesque earned the shutout in net for the Vineyard. Nauset 1, Middleboro 1: Junior Mackenzie Meads scored in the first half and the Sachems knotted things late in a non-league tie in Middleboro. Meads’ shot from the right side, top of the circle, went to the Middleboro goalies right and in for a 1-0 Nauset lead with 12:19 to play in the opening half. The Sachems tied the game with 13 minutes to play, with neither side netting the game-winner. Junior Lucy McNamara kept things close for the Warriors with strong play in net, while getting key defensive support from senior Tanner Deegan and freshman Eliza Campbell. GOLF Martha’s Vineyard qualifies for tournament: Chris Mayhew, Finn Simpkins and Kaitlin Marchand all shot four-over 39s at Farm Neck to help the Vineyarders beat Whitman-Hanson 241-249, earning the island team a berth in the Div. 3 South Tournament. The Div. 3 South Tournament is scheduled for Monday, Oct. 19 at Dennis Highlands. By Cape Cod Times
